  "body": "Extracted from #31475, quoting @gsmet:\r\n\r\n> Dialect compatibility - Still undecided on this one, should we try to migrate people to the new dialects automatically or not? (should probably be moved to a separate issue at some point but might be part of this compatibility work so dropping it here for now)\r\n\r\nRelates to #31474, where we'll expose a configurable min-db-version. We could use the configured dialect to infer that version, e.g. `org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQL10Dialect` would be `db-kind=postgresql` + `min-db-version=10.0`.",
